# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# live-diagnosis-organ.form — an organ that diagnoses any live program through
#   its open channels: the framebuffer (per-op execution counts, printed live by
#   the emitted binaries), the value channel (outputs over inputs), and the
#   substrate ground (what the recipe IS). It LEARNS the program's law from the
#   data, independently PREDICTS it from the recipe, and holds conviction only
#   when the two witnesses agree. Recipe and data stay separate throughout.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Urs: "assembly to source and to any language grammar emitter can be observed
# via the framebuffer live. we can build an organ that can use the framebuffer to
# diagnose live any program and reason about any cell or recipe via the substrate
# and any open channel. I would assume the asm channel needs to be learned and
# the recipe and data separate."
#
# The tissue was already grown: the walker binaries the 4th kernel emits PRINT
# their fk_arms per-op execution counts — that IS the live framebuffer; and the
# fib tree carries the same universal tag space in the native compiler
# (form-lower) and the walker (fourth-walker-emit). One recipe, two carriers,
# two open channels — the organ reads both.

(live-diagnosis-organ

  (lineage
    (organ         form-stdlib/form-diagnose.fk)        # the generic diagnosis recipe
    (framebuffer   fourth-walker-emit.fk)                # fk_arms printed live by every walker binary
    (value-channel form-to-asm.form)                     # the native binary's outputs over inputs
    (ground        coherence-substrate)                  # the recipe/tree — what the program IS
    (witness-law   witness-theorem.form)                 # fired / refuted / SILENT — now inside one program
    (senses-for    core-lift + JIT)                      # hot ops are lift candidates; the readout feeds the loop
    (proof-band    tests/form-diagnose-band.fk)          # 31 three-way, every diagnosis two-sided
    (live-witness  scripts/form_diagnose_demo.sh))       # real binaries, real channels, conviction live

  # ── The channels — every emitter is observable live ──────────────────
  # Assembly emission, source emission, any-grammar emission: all run through
  # kernels whose binaries carry the framebuffer. The walker prints fk_arms after
  # every run — per-op-tag execution counts, the program's own breath made
  # visible. The native binary speaks through its value channel. Both are OPEN:
  # anything that can read a number can read them.
  (channels
    (framebuffer  "(tag count) rows — fk_arms, printed live by the emitted walker binaries")
    (value        "outputs over inputs — the native binary's exit codes, measured not asserted")
    (substrate    "the recipe tree itself — structural ground, readable without any run")
    (witnessed    "fib(10)=55 walked live: ARG fired 442×, CALL 176×, LE/COND 177× — the real breath"))

  # ── The diagnoses ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (diagnoses
    (hot     "the highest-fired op — the JIT / core-lift candidate (found live: ARG)")
    (dead    "a tag present in the recipe that NEVER fired — the witness theorem's
              silence-state surfacing inside a single program; untested tissue named")
    (learned "the law inferred from the value channel ALONE — no tree access:
              obs[i] = obs[i-1] + obs[i-2] learned from the exit codes 1,2,3,5,8,13")
    (ground  "the law predicted from the recipe ALONE — no run access: the tree's
              COND else = ADD(CALL, CALL) predicts an order-2 additive recurrence")
    (convict "learned AND ground agree — two INDEPENDENT witnesses, one truth;
              a straight-line program cannot reach conviction on the recursive law"))

  # ── The learned channel — and why recipe/data separation is the law ──
  # The asm/behavior channel is LEARNED, not hardcoded: the organ infers what a
  # program does from its observable behavior (data), then checks the inference
  # against the substrate's structural ground (recipe). The organ itself is ONE
  # generic recipe — every framebuffer row, observation vector, and learned law
  # is data passing through it. This separation is what makes the learning safe:
  # a learned claim alone is a hypothesis; a structural claim alone is untested;
  # conviction requires both. (The same two-witness shape as the byte-conviction
  # gate, and the form-to-asm witness ladder: a wrong reference passes matching;
  # only an independent witness refutes it.)
  (learned-channel
    (learn       "behavior inferred from observation — the data side, channel by channel")
    (ground      "structure read from the substrate — the recipe side, no run needed")
    (separate    "one generic organ recipe; observations and learned laws are always data")
    (convict     "agreement of the independent witnesses — never either alone"))

  # ── Source-symbol lookup — REALIZED: the per-NODE framebuffer ────────
  # The spy walker (fkc-emit-spy) counts fk_hits per TABLE ROW — finer than
  # fk_arms' per-op counts — and row i IS source node i, so framebuffer
  # inspection joins directly to source symbols: every node's live hit count,
  # rendered by any pack at any level. Witnessed on a running fib(10): 177
  # function entries (IF/LE/ARG each 177), 89 leaf returns, 88 recursive
  # expansions — 89 + 88 = 177, the call-tree arithmetic READABLE straight off
  # the framebuffer; zero dead nodes (full coverage). One engine: the spy walk
  # reuses the standard arm text; only the header gains the per-node count.
  (symbol-lookup-realized
    (channel   "fk_hits[i] per table row — the per-node framebuffer (fkc-emit-spy)")
    (join      "hits[i] -> source node i -> any pack's rendering — lookup is total")
    (verbs     "fd-vhot (hottest node) · fd-vdead (never-executed nodes) · fd-vat (point lookup)")
    (witnessed "fib(10)=55 live: hot node named; 89 leaves + 88 internal = 177 calls
                read off the counts; scripts/form_symbol_demo.sh prints the full table")
    (band      "tests/form-spy-band.fk -> 31 three-way — emission carries the counter,
                one engine with the standard walk, hot/dead two-sided, deterministic"))

  # ── Cell provenance — REALIZED: row -> original source file:line:col ──
  # The locator (form-provenance.fk) needs only the source text: every (fk-
  # constructor makes exactly one cell, and flatten is deterministic post-order,
  # so scanning constructors (pre-order with depth) and converting to post-order
  # yields, for table row k, the byte offset / line / column that AUTHORED it.
  # No kernel surgery, no side table to drift — the source and the table align
  # structurally. Witnessed live: every cell of a running fib binary answers
  # "which source line created me", and the two recursive CALL SITES are
  # distinguished by line (6:18 the n-1 call, 7:18 the n-2 call) — per-site
  # resolution per-tag counting can never reach. Companions: the kernels'
  # fatals already name the Form line that produced them (the runtime half);
  # the kernel-level NodeID provenance plane is the named destination.
  (cell-provenance-realized
    (locator   "fp-locate: source text -> per-row constructor offsets; fp-line/fp-col")
    (total     "one location per table row — count equals the flattened row count")
    (no-drift  "post-order of the source scan IS flatten's row order — structural alignment")
    (witnessed "hits -> row -> fib-source.fk:line:col -> the line itself, live
                (scripts/form_provenance_demo.sh); call sites told apart by line")
    (band      "tests/form-provenance-band.fk -> 31 three-way — total, exact offsets,
                subtrees land together, line/col, two-sided (non-ctors add nothing)")
    (scope     "fk-* constructor expressions; parens inside string literals are outside
                this scope; the in-cell kernel provenance plane is the destination"))

  # ── Closing cells ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (closing-cells
    (more-laws    "beyond order-2 additive: multiplicative, affine, periodic — a law
                   LIBRARY the organ tries against any channel (auto-research over laws)")
    (live-stream  "the framebuffer as a continuous stream (the /api/_form observation
                   doors) rather than an end-of-run print — diagnosis DURING the run")
    (channel-organ "wiring the diagnosis into form-os-channel: the organ's findings
                   become offered expansions (hot op -> lift proposal) we satsang-validate")
    (any-binary   "learning the channel of a FOREIGN binary (no recipe ground available):
                   diagnosis degrades honestly to hypothesis — named, never asserted"))

  (invariant
    (every-emitter-is-observable-live      the-framebuffer-is-the-programs-own-breath)
    (the-organ-is-one-generic-recipe       observations-and-laws-are-data-passing-through)
    (the-channel-is-learned-not-hardcoded  behavior-inferred-then-grounded-never-assumed)
    (conviction-needs-two-witnesses        learned-from-data-AND-predicted-from-recipe)
    (silence-is-a-diagnosis                a-never-fired-op-is-named-not-ignored)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to verify
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/form-diagnose.fk \
#     form-stdlib/tests/form-diagnose-band.fk      # → 31 three-way, all diagnoses two-sided
#   bash scripts/form_diagnose_demo.sh             # real channels: native exit codes + live
#                                                  #   fk_arms framebuffer → conviction
